From a712ea347256416f84960e12ea794f87b3dfbb8a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Priyadarshnee Srinivasan <priys@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 28 Jul 2025 10:50:03 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM: PROTOCOL: hostapd: Validate channel and bandwidth
 during power mode configuration

 When the AFC response includes only 160 MHz opclass CFIs and the
AP is configured for 320 MHz bandwidth, the AP correctly operates
in 320 MHz under LPI power mode, as no 320 MHz channels are
present in the AFC response.

However, if the power mode is manually switched to Standard Power
(SP) using the 'set_6ghz_power_mode' command via hostapd_cli, hostapd
continues to operate in 320 MHz under SP mode—despite the AFC response
not authorizing this configuration.

This issue stems from the kernel's SP channel list
construction logic, which marks a channel as SP-allowed if it is
supported by both the PSD and the 20 MHz CFI range. Since the 320 MHz range
satisfies both conditions, it is incorrectly flagged as SP-allowed. The
logic does not explicitly validate the channel CFIs against the
AFC response for the current configured bandwidth.

To address this, hostapd must validate that the channel is explicitly
listed in the AFC response before applying the SP power mode. This ensures
that only AFC-authorized channels are permitted for SP operation.

Fixes: 264ec03e8f2 (r28-hostapd-Add-hostapd-cli- support-to-switch-6GHZ-power.patch)
Patch-work: None
Tag: 6G_REGULATORY
